cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.HC

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for de-identification of humans in video sequences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of 3D models, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of Kinect sensor and its libraries for detecting and localizing human joints suggests the involvement of multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) categories. Finally, the paper also involves steganography, which is a technique for secure communication and falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR).
